{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.simplifyAC\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">simplifyAC</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.ACApps\">ACApps</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> (<a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.ACApps\">ACApps</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.DelayedExpr\">DelayedExpr</a>))</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `e` can be simplified by the AC module, return the simplified term and the proof term of the\nequality. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.simplifyAC","kind":"def","line":627,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.simplifyAC","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L627-L635"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.simplifyACStep\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">simplifyACStep</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.ACApps\">ACApps</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> (<a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.ACApps\">ACApps</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.DelayedExpr\">DelayedExpr</a>))</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The single step of `simplifyAC`.\n\nSimplifies an expression `e` by either simplifying one argument to the AC operator, or the whole\nexpression. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.simplifyACStep","kind":"def","line":605,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.simplifyACStep","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L605-L625"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.simplifyACCore\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">simplifyACCore</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e </span><span class=\"fn\">lhs </span><span class=\"fn\">rhs</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.ACApps\">ACApps</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">H</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.DelayedExpr\">DelayedExpr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> (<a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.ACApps\">ACApps</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.DelayedExpr\">DelayedExpr</a>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given `e := lhs * r` and `H : lhs = rhs`, return `rhs * r` and the proof of `e = rhs * r`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.simplifyACCore","kind":"def","line":589,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.simplifyACCore","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L589-L603"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkACSimpProof\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkACSimpProof</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">tr </span><span class=\"fn\">t </span><span class=\"fn\">s </span><span class=\"fn\">r </span><span class=\"fn\">sr</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.ACApps\">ACApps</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">tEqs</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.DelayedExpr\">DelayedExpr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Basic.html#Lean.Meta.MetaM\">Lean.MetaM</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.DelayedExpr\">DelayedExpr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given `tr := t*r` `sr := s*r` `tEqs : t = s`, return a proof for `tr = sr`\n\nWe use `a*b` to denote an AC application. That is, `(a*b)*(c*a)` is the term `a*a*b*c`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkACSimpProof","kind":"def","line":565,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkACSimpProof","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L565-L587"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkACProof\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkACProof</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">e₂</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Basic.html#Lean.Meta.MetaM\">Lean.MetaM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Return the proof of `e₁ = e₂` using `ac_rfl` tactic. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkACProof","kind":"def","line":557,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkACProof","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L557-L563"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkNeOfNeOfEq\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkNeOfNeOfEq</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">aNeB₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">b₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given `aNeB₁ : a ≠ b₁`, `b₁` and `b`, return a proof of `a ≠ b` if `b` and `b₁` are in the\nsame equivalence class. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkNeOfNeOfEq","kind":"def","line":546,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkNeOfNeOfEq","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L546-L555"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkNeOfEqOfNe\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkNeOfEqOfNe</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">a₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">a₁NeB</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given `a`, `a₁` and `a₁NeB : a₁ ≠ b`, return a proof of `a ≠ b` if `a` and `a₁` are in the\nsame equivalence class. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkNeOfEqOfNe","kind":"def","line":535,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkNeOfEqOfNe","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L535-L544"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getInconsistencyProof\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">getInconsistencyProof</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Build a proof of `False` if the context is inconsistent.\nReturns `none` if `False` is not known to be true. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getInconsistencyProof","kind":"def","line":526,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getInconsistencyProof","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L526-L533"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getPropEqProof\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">getPropEqProof</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Build a proof for `a = b`. Fails if `a` and `b` are not known to be equal. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getPropEqProof","kind":"def","line":520,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getPropEqProof","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L520-L524"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getEqFalseProof\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">getEqFalseProof</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Build a proof for `e = False`. Fails if `e` is not known to be false. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getEqFalseProof","kind":"def","line":514,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getEqFalseProof","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L514-L518"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getEqTrueProof\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">getEqTrueProof</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Build a proof for `e = True`. Fails if `e` is not known to be true. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getEqTrueProof","kind":"def","line":508,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getEqTrueProof","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L508-L512"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">partial def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getHEqProof\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">getHEqProof</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">e₂</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Build a proof for `e₁ ≍ e₂`.\nThe result is `none` if `e₁` and `e₂` are not in the same equivalence class. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getHEqProof","kind":"opaque","line":501,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getHEqProof","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L501-L505"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">partial def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getEqProof\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">getEqProof</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">e₂</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Build a proof for `e₁ = e₂`.\nThe result is `none` if `e₁` and `e₂` are not in the same equivalence class. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getEqProof","kind":"opaque","line":495,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getEqProof","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L495-L499"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">partial def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getEqProofCore\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">getEqProofCore</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">e₂</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">asHEq</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `asHEq` is `true`, then build a proof for `e₁ ≍ e₂`.\nOtherwise, build a proof for `e₁ = e₂`.\nThe result is `none` if `e₁` and `e₂` are not in the same equivalence class. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getEqProofCore","kind":"opaque","line":422,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getEqProofCore","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L422-L493"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">partial def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkProof\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkProof</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">lhs </span><span class=\"fn\">rhs</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">H</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.EntryExpr\">EntryExpr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">heqProofs</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Use the format of `H` to try and construct a proof or `lhs = rhs`:\n* If `H = .congr`, then use congruence.\n* If `H = .eqTrue`, try to prove `lhs = True` or `rhs = True`,\n  if they have the format `R a b`, by proving `a = b`.\n* Otherwise, return the (delayed) proof encoded by `H` itself. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkProof","kind":"opaque","line":386,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkProof","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L386-L420"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">partial def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkDelayedProof\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkDelayedProof</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">H</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.DelayedExpr\">DelayedExpr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Turn a delayed proof into an actual proof term. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkDelayedProof","kind":"opaque","line":368,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkDelayedProof","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L368-L384"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">partial def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkCongrProof\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkCongrProof</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">e₂</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">heqProofs</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Use congruence on arguments to prove `e₁ = e₂`.\n\nSpecial case: if `e₁` and `e₂` have the form `R lhs₁ rhs₁` and `R lhs₂ rhs₂` such that\n`R` is symmetric and `lhs₁ = rhs₂`, then use those facts instead. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkCongrProof","kind":"opaque","line":358,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkCongrProof","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L358-L366"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">partial def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkSymmCongrProof\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkSymmCongrProof</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">e₂</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">heqProofs</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `e₁ : R lhs₁ rhs₁`, `e₂ : R lhs₂ rhs₂` and `lhs₁ = rhs₂`, where `R` is a symmetric relation,\nprove `R lhs₁ rhs₁` is equivalent to `R lhs₂ rhs₂`.\n\n* if `lhs₁` is known to equal `lhs₂`, return `none`\n* if `lhs₁` is not known to equal `rhs₂`, fail. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkSymmCongrProof","kind":"opaque","line":323,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkSymmCongrProof","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L323-L356"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">partial def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkCongrProofCore\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkCongrProofCore</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">lhs </span><span class=\"fn\">rhs</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">heqProofs</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Use congruence on arguments to prove `lhs = rhs`.\n\nThat is, tries to prove that `lhsFn lhsArgs[0] ... lhsArgs[n-1] = lhsFn rhsArgs[0] ... rhsArgs[n-1]`\nby showing that `lhsArgs[i] = rhsArgs[i]` for all `i`.\n\nFails if the head function of `lhs` is not that of `rhs`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkCongrProofCore","kind":"opaque","line":244,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkCongrProofCore","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L244-L321"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkTransOpt\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkTransOpt</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">H₁?</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">H₂</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">heqProofs</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Basic.html#Lean.Meta.MetaM\">Lean.MetaM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Apply transitivity to `H₁?` and `H₂`, which are both `Eq` or `HEq` depending on `heqProofs`.\n\nIf `H₁?` is `none`, return `H₂` instead. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkTransOpt","kind":"def","line":235,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkTransOpt","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L235-L241"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkTrans\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkTrans</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">H₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">H₂</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">heqProofs</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Basic.html#Lean.Meta.MetaM\">Lean.MetaM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Apply transitivity to `H₁` and `H₂`, which are both `Eq` or `HEq` depending on `heqProofs`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkTrans","kind":"def","line":231,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkTrans","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L231-L233"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isEqFalse\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">isEqFalse</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Is the proposition `e` known to be false? ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isEqFalse","kind":"def","line":226,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isEqFalse","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L226-L229"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isEqTrue\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">isEqTrue</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Is the proposition `e` known to be true? ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isEqTrue","kind":"def","line":221,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isEqTrue","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L221-L224"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isNotEqv\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">isNotEqv</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">e₂</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Is `e₁ ≠ e₂` known to be true?\n\nNote that this is stronger than `not (isEqv e₁ e₂)`:\nonly if we can prove they are distinct this returns `true`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isNotEqv","kind":"def","line":211,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isNotEqv","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L211-L219"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isEqv\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">isEqv</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">e₂</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Are `e₁` and `e₂` known to be in the same equivalence class? ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isEqv","kind":"def","line":205,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isEqv","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L205-L209"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.flipProof\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">flipProof</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">H</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.EntryExpr\">EntryExpr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">flipped </span><span class=\"fn\">heqProofs</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.EntryExpr\">EntryExpr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Apply symmetry to `H`, which is an `Eq` or a `HEq`.\n\n* If `heqProofs` is true, ensure the result is a `HEq` (otherwise it is assumed to be `Eq`).\n* If `flipped` is true, apply `symm`, otherwise keep the same direction. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.flipProof","kind":"def","line":195,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.flipProof","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L195-L203"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.flipDelayedProofCore\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">flipDelayedProofCore</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">H</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.DelayedExpr\">DelayedExpr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">flipped </span><span class=\"fn\">heqProofs</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.DelayedExpr\">DelayedExpr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"In a delayed way, apply symmetry to `H`, which is an `Eq` or a `HEq`.\n\n* If `heqProofs` is true, ensure the result is a `HEq` (otherwise it is assumed to be `Eq`).\n* If `flipped` is true, apply `symm`, otherwise keep the same direction. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.flipDelayedProofCore","kind":"def","line":180,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.flipDelayedProofCore","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L180-L193"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.flipProofCore\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">flipProofCore</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">H</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">flipped </span><span class=\"fn\">heqProofs</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Apply symmetry to `H`, which is an `Eq` or a `HEq`.\n\n* If `heqProofs` is true, ensure the result is a `HEq` (otherwise it is assumed to be `Eq`).\n* If `flipped` is true, apply `symm`, otherwise keep the same direction. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.flipProofCore","kind":"def","line":165,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.flipProofCore","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L165-L178"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.hasHEqProofs\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">hasHEqProofs</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">root</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Does the congruence class with root `root` have any `HEq` proofs? ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.hasHEqProofs","kind":"def","line":159,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.hasHEqProofs","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L159-L163"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">partial def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.updateMT\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">C