\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkCCCongrTheorem\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkCCCongrTheorem</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCCongrTheorem\">CCCongrTheorem</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Try to find a congruence theorem for the expression `e` with support for `HEq`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkCCCongrTheorem","kind":"def","line":135,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkCCCongrTheorem","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L135-L139"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkCCHCongrTheorem\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkCCHCongrTheorem</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">fn</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">nargs</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/Datatypes.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCCongrTheorem\">CCCongrTheorem</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Try to find a congruence theorem for an application of `fn` with `nargs` arguments, with support\nfor `HEq`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkCCHCongrTheorem","kind":"def","line":114,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.mkCCHCongrTheorem","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L114-L133"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">partial def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isCongruent\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">isCongruent</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">e₂</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Return true iff the given function application are congruent\n\n`e₁` should have the form `f a` and `e₂` the form `g b`.\n\nSee paper: Congruence Closure for Intensional Type Theory. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isCongruent","kind":"opaque","line":64,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isCongruent","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L64-L112"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isCgRoot\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">isCgRoot</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Is `e` the root of its congruence class? ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isCgRoot","kind":"def","line":60,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.isCgRoot","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.lean#L60-L62"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM.getRoot\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">CC</span>.<span class=\"name\">CCM</span>.<span class=\"name\">getRoot</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tactic.CC.CCM\">CCM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Return the root expression of the expression's congruence class. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/CC/MkProof.html#Mathlib.Tacti